Genes encoding proteins that control the antiviral defences of interferons were found to have early loss of function in severe coronavirus illness. The patients suffer hypoxiaemic symptoms and die from insufficient supply of oxygen. In a study published under accelerated peer review in the journal Nature, the genetic basis for susceptibility to critical Covid-19 illness has been reported.
The virus presents as mild, moderate or severe case and the study found that, critically ill patients have unique pathophysiology. The study recruited 2,444 critically ill patients across 208 intensive care units in the UK.



