Using a technology known as genetics of mortality in critical ill care (GeOMICC), the scientists carried out whole blood DNA analysis of blood to perform genome wide associations studies that seek to pinpoint specific genes with disease susceptibility. Two important conclusions were inferred.
First, genes for Covid-19 critical illness are heritable and, therefore, people possessing them were more likely to suffer critical illness when infected with the virus. Secondly, repurposing of existing drugs could potentially reduce mortality in critically ill patients.



