Genes encoding proteins that control the antiviral defences of interferons were found to have early loss of function in severe coronavirus illness.
This loss of antiviral defences was associated with high lung burden of Sars-Cov2, the virus causing Covid-19. Paradoxically, administration of exogenous interferon to restore antiviral activities in the lungs of the patients did not improve the patients’ lung capacity, indicating delayed use of synthetic interferons isn’t helpful at advanced stage of the illness.
Pulmonary inflammation
This demonstrates the need to perform GeOMICC tests in patients so that those with mild and moderate illnesses can be put into exogenous interferon treatment since it’s likely to be effective prior to loss of function of interferon genes that occurs with onset of critical illness.



